    public interface IMarketDataValue
    Basic market data value - consisting of a value and when that value was set.

    Data can be long or BytesSegment or String.
    Only one value should be set at any time.
    The other undefined values will be set as follows:

    • String - null
    • long - IInstrument.VALUE_UNKNOWN
    • BytesSegment - null or length of segment < 0
    The value that is set (if any) is indicated by getDefinedValueType() which returns a small int corresponding to the defined data type: long, bytes or String.

    See interface definition for constants for these type ints.

    Retrieving the defined value

    If you do not already know the expected type of the data, use code like the following. 
     IMarketDataValue mdv;
      :
      switch (mdv.getDefinedValueType()) {
      case IMarketDataValue.MD_TYPE_UNDEFINED:
        //Process undefined value
        break;
 
      case IMarketDataValue.MD_TYPE_BYTES:
        BytesSegment bytesValue = mdv.getBytesSegmentValue();
        //Process bytes value
        break;
 
      case IMarketDataValue.MD_TYPE_LONG:
        long longValue = mdv.getLongValue();
        //Process long value
        break;
 
      case IMarketDataValue.MD_TYPE_STRING:
        String.value = mdv.getStringValue();
        //Process String value
        break;
      }
